/* 
jQuerySF is a JS conference coming up in SF that 
will be featuring a gallery of "generative art"
(art that is generated with code, often animated).
I told the conference organizers that y'all are great
at making generative art here on Khan Academy,
and they're excited about showing off your creations
on the giant screens.

For this contest, spin-off this program and replace it
with your own generative art, or, if you already have
a generative art program or want to use the webpage environment,
write in big text() "Check out my program X!" and include 
the URL to your other program.

I'd like to share a little bit about the program creators
when we display the programs at the conference,
so please say what country/state you're from,
what grade you're in (if in school),
and answer "What do you love about programming?"
(Skip any of those details you're not allowed
or comfortable with sharing them!)

Deadline is June 17th. You may submit multiple programs.
I will select a number of programs to display at jQuerySF
and give a Golden Winston to each of those programs' creators.
*/
